In Heritrix 1.x, it&#39;s essentially always a CandidateURI (and sometimes 
also a CrawlURI).

In Heritrix 2.0, it&#39;s defined as a ProcessorURI (instead of Object) and 
  outside of unit tests, should always be a CrawlURI.

- Gordon @ IA

