&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; A similar procedure but with a &#39;[classname].subclasses&#39; file applies in 
&gt;&gt; 2.0.x and is mentioned here:
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; http://tech.groups.yahoo.com/group/archive-crawler/message/5268 
&gt;&gt; &lt;http://tech.groups.yahoo.com/group/archive-crawler/message/5268&gt;
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; (Also in 2.0, you can type the fully-qualified name of any class on the 
&gt;&gt; classpath to add it in the web UI.)
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; The approach may change slightly again in 2.2 and beyond, but we will 
&gt;&gt; definitely maintain the ability to type the full name of any desired 
